# FinScoreX Environment Variables for Vercel + Supabase

# Database (Supabase)
# Get this from: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > Database > Connection string > URI
# Replace [YOUR-PASSWORD] with your actual database password
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@db.[PROJECT-REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres"

# JWT Secret (Generate a random 64-character string)
JWT_SECRET="your-super-secret-jwt-key-at-least-64-characters-long-for-security"

# Session Secret (Generate a random 64-character string)
SESSION_SECRET="your-super-secret-session-key-at-least-64-characters-long-for-security"

# Environment
NODE_ENV="production"

# ===================================
# INSTRUCTIONS FOR VERCEL DEPLOYMENT
# ===================================

# 1. Create a Supabase project:
#    - Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
#    - Create new project
#    - Wait for setup to complete

# 2. Get your DATABASE_URL:
#    - In Supabase: Settings > Database
#    - Copy "Connection string" under "Connection pooling"
#    - Replace [YOUR-PASSWORD] with your database password

# 3. Generate secrets:
#    - JWT_SECRET: Use a secure random generator (64+ characters)
#    - SESSION_SECRET: Use a secure random generator (64+ characters)

# 4. Deploy to Vercel:
#    - Connect your GitHub repo to Vercel
#    - Add these environment variables in Vercel dashboard
#    - Deploy

# 5. Run database migrations:
#    - After first deployment, run: npm run db:push
#    - This creates all necessary tables in Supabase